                             CURSOR
                            ========

      Cursor is a private sql memory area which is used to process
multiple records and also this is an record by record process.


  *         /To process multiple records.
 *** CURSOR
  *         \record by record process.


    

    cursor having following 5 step proces. 
These are.

1)declare
2)open
3)fetch
4)close
5)deallocate

1)Declare:-
==========
   in declare section of the T-SQL block we are declaring
the cursor by using following syntax.

syntax:-
=======
declare cursorname cursor for select * from tablename
where condition;

ex:-
===
declare c1 cursor for select * from emp
    where job='CLERK';

2)open:-whenever we are opening the cursor then only SQL server
======  retrieve data from table into cursor memory area because in all
        relational databases whenever we are opening the cursor then
        only cursor select statement are executed.

syntax:-
======
open cursorname;


NOTE:-When a cursor is opened, the cursor pointer is positioned 
====  before the first record in the cursor’s memory area.


3)fetch:-(fetching data from cursor memory area)
================================================
  By using fetch statement we are fetching data from cursor memory
area into T-SQL variables

syntax:-
=======
fetch next from cursorname into variablename1,variablename2;


4)close:-
=========

syntax:-
=======
close cursorname

5)deallocating cursor:-
=====================

syntax:-
======
deallocate cursorname
 

